# The Spark API hierarchy

## Three structured APIs, low → high

- **RDD** — original, functional, row-by-row — **no Catalyst, no Tungsten**
- **DataFrame** — a distributed table with a schema — the everyday API
- **Dataset[T]** — a typed DataFrame, compile-time safety — **Scala / Java only**

## In PySpark

- You only get **DataFrames** — internally just `Dataset[Row]` (no static type param)

## The fact that matters

- **SQL, DataFrame, and Dataset all compile through Catalyst** → identical plans
- Only **RDD bypasses Catalyst** — why it's slower on structured data
